laboratory_examinations.findings: The formation of the medial first toe was hypoplastic, and only traces of the phalanges with a normal first metatarsal appeared on a radiograph.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Postoperative radiograph showed favorable growth of the nail plate and phalangeal bone three years after surgery.
